metadata.name: Fronteras en abstracto #58
metadata.description:
A place in the abstract, walking in one direction without knowing if you will reach that place. Then, in case you find it, go to the other side before dawn.

It's just a game of words and phrases that have to be given meaning, and we find it on the frontier of something that we don't know what it is.

//

Un lugar en abstracto, caminando en una dirección sin saber si se llega a ese lugar. Luego, en caso de encontrarlo, pasar al otro lado antes del amanecer.

Es solo un juego de palabras y frases a las cuales hay que darles sentido, y lo encontramos en la frontera de algo que no sabemos qué es.

//

metadata.name: Sketches of a Drunk #2
metadata.description:
Sketches of a Drunk is a homage to my sketchbooks, chalkboards and scraps of paper that I fill when a few drinks get my creative juices flowing.

Six different color palettes, various grid sizes and subdivisions, different densities and various shapes and shading patterns open up infinite possibilities.

metadata.name: Caterpillars #103
metadata.description:
DISCLAIMER : 
I have started coding about 4 months ago and I am not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside. 

This will be kind of a charity project where the PRIMARY SALES will be 
divided as follows:
 - 60 % of primary sales will go to "Askida Fatura" -> https://askidafatura.ibb.gov.tr/
 - 20 % will go to Processing Foundation -> https://processingfoundation.org/
 - 20 % will go to Coding Train -> https://twitter.com/thecodingtrain

"Askida Fatura" is run by Istanbul Municipality and is a campaign that is used for paying the utility bills of the less fortunate living in Istanbul. On average, a couple of tezos pays one bill, and I hope to pay 5 - 10 bills with this.

I will figure out the best way to transfer the amounts later this week and the upcoming weeks, and will provide proof of transfer via my twitter. 

SINCE THIS IS CHARITY, I WILL NOT BE BURNING THE REMAINING EDITIONS!!!

Still, if you dont like what you got ping me and you can get your refund. 

twitter : https://twitter.com/evilnft
fxhash : https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/evilnft
objkt : https://objkt.com/profile/evilnft/created

about Caterpillars,

This is a humble project, does not try to achieve too much, and also wants you to not expect too much from it. 

features : 
 - 8 palettes
 - 2 different origins
 - 5 different characters
 - 6 to 49 sections
 - should be responsive, although I have only tested this on computers...

 press "s" to save a png.

metadata.name: The Ocean Waves #123
metadata.description:
Ocean waves in calm or stormy skies. Spray, and the occasional buoy passes by.

Large and rolling waves are generated at the back and get more turbulent as they get closer to the viewer. A stripe of sunlight varies in position from towards the back to the front. The highest waves create spray. Everyone once and a while, a buoy or two (or more!) will pass by. The background color is related to the buoy color to make it more harmonious.

metadata.name: Sea of Shapes #20
metadata.description:
This program was inspired by the 2022 Genuary prompt "Make a sea of shapes." It is an abstract and geometric representation of water and waves. I tried to capture the many different possible states of a sea (windy, breezy, calm etc.) by changing parameters within the program for different outputs.

Press 'p' while on Live View to save a high quality (4000x4000) png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #39
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: CityScape: Istanbul #88
metadata.description:
Istanbul is a city that straddles the Bosporus Strait, and lies in both Europe and Asia, with a population of over 15 million residents. Most of the population is located in big iconic hills known as the "Seven Hills of Istanbul". 

   In this project, I tried to capture and interpret the daily life routine of the people who live in these hills with the viewing point from Bosphorus. There are three camera angle possibilities to examine the details in different layers. Also, building types, the slope of the hill, and green area density vary in between those scenarios. There are two time zones: day and night. In the night scene, there is a possibility to obtain the crescent moon which is the symbol of the culture inhabits in these lands.

To save as a high-quality image, open in live view and click yes on the incoming prompt.

Created with p5js
